53// A simple closed interval.
54class Interval {
55 public:
56 Interval() : from_(kNone), to_(kNone - 1) {} // '- 1' for branchless size().
57 Interval(int from, int to) : from_(from), to_(to) {}
58 Interval Union(Interval that) {
59 if (that.from_ == kNone) return *this;
60 if (from_ == kNone) return that;
61 return Interval(std::min(from_, that.from_), std::max(to_, that.to_));
62 }
63
64 static Interval Empty() { return Interval(); }
65
66 bool Contains(int value) const { return (from_ <= value) && (value <= to_); }
67 bool is_empty() const { return from_ == kNone; }
68 int from() const { return from_; }
69 int to() const { return to_; }
70 int size() const { return to_ - from_ + 1; }
71
72 static constexpr int kNone = -1;
73
74 private:
75 int from_;
76 int to_;
77};

79// Named standard character sets.
80enum class StandardCharacterSet : char {
81 kWhitespace = 's', // Like /\s/.
82 kNotWhitespace = 'S', // Like /\S/.
83 kWord = 'w', // Like /\w/.
84 kNotWord = 'W', // Like /\W/.
85 kDigit = 'd', // Like /\d/.
86 kNotDigit = 'D', // Like /\D/.
87 kLineTerminator = 'n', // The inverse of /./.
88 kNotLineTerminator = '.', // Like /./.
89 kEverything = '*', // Matches every character, like /./s.
90};
91
92// Represents code points (with values up to 0x10FFFF) in the range from from_
93// to to_, both ends are inclusive.
94class CharacterRange {
95 public:
96 CharacterRange() = default;
97 // For compatibility with the CHECK_OK macro.
98 CharacterRange(void* null) { DCHECK_NULL(null); } // NOLINT
99
100 static inline CharacterRange Singleton(base::uc32 value) {
101 return CharacterRange(value, value);
102 }
103 static inline CharacterRange Range(base::uc32 from, base::uc32 to) {
104 DCHECK(0 <= from && to <= kMaxCodePoint);
105 DCHECK(static_cast<uint32_t>(from) <= static_cast<uint32_t>(to));
106 return CharacterRange(from, to);
107 }
108 static inline CharacterRange Everything() {
109 return CharacterRange(0, kMaxCodePoint);
110 }
111
112 static inline ZoneList<CharacterRange>* List(Zone* zone,
113 CharacterRange range) {
114 ZoneList<CharacterRange>* list =
115 zone->New<ZoneList<CharacterRange>>(1, zone);
116 list->Add(range, zone);
117 return list;
118 }
119
120 // Add class escapes. Add case equivalent closure for \w and \W if necessary.
121 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static void AddClassEscape(
122 StandardCharacterSet standard_character_set,
123 ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges, bool add_unicode_case_equivalents,
124 Zone* zone);
125 // Add case equivalents to ranges. Only used for /i, not for /ui or /vi, as
126 // the semantics for unicode mode are slightly different.
127 // See https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-runtime-semantics-canonicalize-ch Note 4.
128 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static void AddCaseEquivalents(
129 Isolate* isolate, Zone* zone, ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges,
130 bool is_one_byte);
131 // Add case equivalent code points to ranges. Only used for /ui and /vi, not
132 // for /i, as the semantics for non-unicode mode are slightly different.
133 // See https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-runtime-semantics-canonicalize-ch Note 4.
134 static void AddUnicodeCaseEquivalents(ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges,
135 Zone* zone);
136
137 bool Contains(base::uc32 i) const { return from_ <= i && i <= to_; }
138 base::uc32 from() const { return from_; }
139 base::uc32 to() const { return to_; }
140 bool IsEverything(base::uc32 max) const { return from_ == 0 && to_ >= max; }
141 bool IsSingleton() const { return from_ == to_; }
142
143 // Whether a range list is in canonical form: Ranges ordered by from value,
144 // and ranges non-overlapping and non-adjacent.
145 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static bool IsCanonical(
146 const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges);
147 // Convert range list to canonical form. The characters covered by the ranges
148 // will still be the same, but no character is in more than one range, and
149 // adjacent ranges are merged. The resulting list may be shorter than the
150 // original, but cannot be longer.
151 static void Canonicalize(ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges);
152 // Negate the contents of a character range in canonical form.
153 static void Negate(const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* src,
154 ZoneList<CharacterRange>* dst, Zone* zone);
155 // Intersect the contents of two character ranges in canonical form.
156 static void Intersect(const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* lhs,
157 const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* rhs,
158 ZoneList<CharacterRange>* dst, Zone* zone);
159 // Subtract the contents of |to_remove| from the contents of |src|.
160 static void Subtract(const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* src,
161 const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* to_remove,
162 ZoneList<CharacterRange>* dst, Zone* zone);
163 // Remove all ranges outside the one-byte range.
164 static void ClampToOneByte(ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges);
165 // Checks if two ranges (both need to be canonical) are equal.
166 static bool Equals(const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* lhs,
167 const ZoneList<CharacterRange>* rhs);
168
169 private:
170 CharacterRange(base::uc32 from, base::uc32 to) : from_(from), to_(to) {}
171
172 static constexpr int kMaxCodePoint = 0x10ffff;
173
174 base::uc32 from_ = 0;
175 base::uc32 to_ = 0;
176};
177
178inline bool operator==(const CharacterRange& lhs, const CharacterRange& rhs) {
179 return lhs.from() == rhs.from() && lhs.to() == rhs.to();
180}
181inline bool operator!=(const CharacterRange& lhs, const CharacterRange& rhs) {
182 return !operator==(lhs, rhs);
183}

185#define DECL_BOILERPLATE(Name) \
186 void* Accept(RegExpVisitor* visitor, void* data) override; \
187 RegExpNode* ToNode(RegExpCompiler* compiler, RegExpNode* on_success) \
188 override; \
189 RegExp##Name* As##Name() override; \
190 bool Is##Name() override
191
192class RegExpTree : public ZoneObject {
193 public:
194 static const int kInfinity = kMaxInt;
195 virtual ~RegExpTree() = default;
196 virtual void* Accept(RegExpVisitor* visitor, void* data) = 0;
197 virtual RegExpNode* ToNode(RegExpCompiler* compiler,
198 RegExpNode* on_success) = 0;
199 virtual bool IsTextElement() { return false; }
200 virtual bool IsAnchoredAtStart() { return false; }
201 virtual bool IsAnchoredAtEnd() { return false; }
202 virtual int min_match() = 0;
203 virtual int max_match() = 0;
204 // Returns the interval of registers used for captures within this
205 // expression.
206 virtual Interval CaptureRegisters() { return Interval::Empty(); }
207 virtual void AppendToText(RegExpText* text, Zone* zone);
208 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& Print(std::ostream& os, Zone* zone);
209#define MAKE_ASTYPE(Name) \
210 virtual RegExp##Name* As##Name(); \
211 virtual bool Is##Name();
212 FOR_EACH_REG_EXP_TREE_TYPE(MAKE_ASTYPE)
213#undef MAKE_ASTYPE
214};

306class RegExpClassRanges final : public RegExpTree {
307 public:
308 // NEGATED: The character class is negated and should match everything but
309 // the specified ranges.
310 // CONTAINS_SPLIT_SURROGATE: The character class contains part of a split
311 // surrogate and should not be unicode-desugared (crbug.com/641091).
312 // IS_CASE_FOLDED: If case folding is required (/i), it was already
313 // performed on individual ranges and should not be applied again.
314 enum Flag {
315 NEGATED = 1 << 0,
316 CONTAINS_SPLIT_SURROGATE = 1 << 1,
317 IS_CASE_FOLDED = 1 << 2,
318 };
319 using ClassRangesFlags = base::Flags<Flag>;
320
321 RegExpClassRanges(Zone* zone, ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges,
322 ClassRangesFlags class_ranges_flags = ClassRangesFlags())
323 : set_(ranges), class_ranges_flags_(class_ranges_flags) {
324 // Convert the empty set of ranges to the negated Everything() range.
325 if (ranges->is_empty()) {
326 ranges->Add(CharacterRange::Everything(), zone);
327 class_ranges_flags_ ^= NEGATED;
328 }
329 }
330 explicit RegExpClassRanges(StandardCharacterSet standard_set_type)
331 : set_(standard_set_type), class_ranges_flags_() {}
332
333 DECL_BOILERPLATE(ClassRanges);
334
335 bool IsTextElement() override { return true; }
336 int min_match() override { return 1; }
337 // The character class may match two code units for unicode regexps.
338 // TODO(yangguo): we should split this class for usage in TextElement, and
339 // make max_match() dependent on the character class content.
340 int max_match() override { return 2; }
341
342 void AppendToText(RegExpText* text, Zone* zone) override;
343
344 // TODO(lrn): Remove need for complex version if is_standard that
345 // recognizes a mangled standard set and just do { return set_.is_special(); }
346 bool is_standard(Zone* zone);
347 // Returns a value representing the standard character set if is_standard()
348 // returns true.
349 StandardCharacterSet standard_type() const {
350 return set_.standard_set_type();
351 }
352
353 CharacterSet character_set() const { return set_; }
354 ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges(Zone* zone) { return set_.ranges(zone); }
355
356 bool is_negated() const { return (class_ranges_flags_ & NEGATED) != 0; }
357 bool contains_split_surrogate() const {
358 return (class_ranges_flags_ & CONTAINS_SPLIT_SURROGATE) != 0;
359 }
360 bool is_case_folded() const {
361 return (class_ranges_flags_ & IS_CASE_FOLDED) != 0;
362 }
363
364 private:
365 CharacterSet set_;
366 ClassRangesFlags class_ranges_flags_;
367};

369struct CharacterClassStringLess {
370 bool operator()(base::Vector<const base::uc32> lhs,
371 base::Vector<const base::uc32> rhs) const {
372 // Longer strings first so we generate matches for the largest string
373 // possible.
374 if (lhs.length() != rhs.length()) {
375 return lhs.length() > rhs.length();
376 }
377 for (int i = 0; i < lhs.length(); i++) {
378 if (lhs[i] != rhs[i]) {
379 return lhs[i] < rhs[i];
380 }
381 }
382 return false;
383 }
384};
385
386// A type used for strings as part of character classes (only possible in
387// unicode sets mode).
388// We use a ZoneMap instead of an UnorderedZoneMap because we need to match
389// the longest alternatives first. By using a ZoneMap with the custom comparator
390// we can avoid sorting before assembling the code.
391// Strings are likely short (the largest string in current unicode properties
392// consists of 10 code points).
393using CharacterClassStrings = ZoneMap<base::Vector<const base::uc32>,
394 RegExpTree*, CharacterClassStringLess>;
395
396// TODO(pthier): If we are sure we don't want to use icu::UnicodeSets
397// (performance evaluation pending), this class can be merged with
398// RegExpClassRanges.
399class RegExpClassSetOperand final : public RegExpTree {
400 public:
401 RegExpClassSetOperand(ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges,
402 CharacterClassStrings* strings);
403
404 DECL_BOILERPLATE(ClassSetOperand);
405
406 bool IsTextElement() override { return true; }
407 int min_match() override { return min_match_; }
408 int max_match() override { return max_match_; }
409
410 void Union(RegExpClassSetOperand* other, Zone* zone);
411 void Intersect(RegExpClassSetOperand* other,
412 ZoneList<CharacterRange>* temp_ranges, Zone* zone);
413 void Subtract(RegExpClassSetOperand* other,
414 ZoneList<CharacterRange>* temp_ranges, Zone* zone);
415
416 bool has_strings() const { return strings_ != nullptr && !strings_->empty(); }
417 ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges() { return ranges_; }
418 CharacterClassStrings* strings() {
419 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(strings_);
420 return strings_;
421 }
422
423 private:
424 ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges_;
425 CharacterClassStrings* strings_;
426 int min_match_;
427 int max_match_;
428};

430class RegExpClassSetExpression final : public RegExpTree {
431 public:
432 enum class OperationType { kUnion, kIntersection, kSubtraction };
433
434 RegExpClassSetExpression(OperationType op, bool is_negated,
435 bool may_contain_strings,
436 ZoneList<RegExpTree*>* operands);
437
438 DECL_BOILERPLATE(ClassSetExpression);
439
440 // Create an empty class set expression (matches everything if |is_negated|,
441 // nothing otherwise).
442 static RegExpClassSetExpression* Empty(Zone* zone, bool is_negated);
443
444 bool IsTextElement() override { return true; }
445 int min_match() override { return 0; }
446 int max_match() override { return max_match_; }
447
448 OperationType operation() const { return operation_; }
449 bool is_negated() const { return is_negated_; }
450 bool may_contain_strings() const { return may_contain_strings_; }
451 const ZoneList<RegExpTree*>* operands() const { return operands_; }
452 ZoneList<RegExpTree*>* operands() { return operands_; }
453
454 private:
455 // Recursively evaluates the tree rooted at |root|, computing the valid
456 // CharacterRanges and strings after applying all set operations.
457 // The original tree will be modified by this method, so don't store pointers
458 // to inner nodes of the tree somewhere else!
459 // Modifying the tree in-place saves memory and speeds up multiple calls of
460 // the method (e.g. when unrolling quantifiers).
461 // |temp_ranges| is used for intermediate results, passed as parameter to
462 // avoid allocating new lists all the time.
463 static RegExpClassSetOperand* ComputeExpression(
464 RegExpTree* root, ZoneList<CharacterRange>* temp_ranges, Zone* zone);
465
466 const OperationType operation_;
467 bool is_negated_;
468 const bool may_contain_strings_;
469 ZoneList<RegExpTree*>* operands_ = nullptr;
470 int max_match_;
471};

547class RegExpQuantifier final : public RegExpTree {
548 public:
549 enum QuantifierType { GREEDY, NON_GREEDY, POSSESSIVE };
550 RegExpQuantifier(int min, int max, QuantifierType type, RegExpTree* body)
551 : body_(body),
552 min_(min),
553 max_(max),
554 quantifier_type_(type) {
555 if (min > 0 && body->min_match() > kInfinity / min) {
556 min_match_ = kInfinity;
557 } else {
558 min_match_ = min * body->min_match();
559 }
560 if (max > 0 && body->max_match() > kInfinity / max) {
561 max_match_ = kInfinity;
562 } else {
563 max_match_ = max * body->max_match();
564 }
565 }
566
567 DECL_BOILERPLATE(Quantifier);
568
569 static RegExpNode* ToNode(int min, int max, bool is_greedy, RegExpTree* body,
570 RegExpCompiler* compiler, RegExpNode* on_success,
571 bool not_at_start = false);
572 Interval CaptureRegisters() override;
573 int min_match() override { return min_match_; }
574 int max_match() override { return max_match_; }
575 int min() const { return min_; }
576 int max() const { return max_; }
577 QuantifierType quantifier_type() const { return quantifier_type_; }
578 bool is_possessive() const { return quantifier_type_ == POSSESSIVE; }
579 bool is_non_greedy() const { return quantifier_type_ == NON_GREEDY; }
580 bool is_greedy() const { return quantifier_type_ == GREEDY; }
581 RegExpTree* body() const { return body_; }
582
583 private:
584 RegExpTree* body_;
585 int min_;
586 int max_;
587 int min_match_;
588 int max_match_;
589 QuantifierType quantifier_type_;
590};

708class RegExpBackReference final : public RegExpTree {
709 public:
710 explicit RegExpBackReference(Zone* zone) : captures_(1, zone) {}
711 explicit RegExpBackReference(RegExpCapture* capture, Zone* zone)
712 : captures_(1, zone) {
713 captures_.Add(capture, zone);
714 }
715
716 DECL_BOILERPLATE(BackReference);
717
718 int min_match() override { return 0; }
719 // The back reference may be recursive, e.g. /(\2)(\1)/. To avoid infinite
720 // recursion, we give up. Ignorance is bliss.
721 int max_match() override { return kInfinity; }
722 const ZoneList<RegExpCapture*>* captures() const { return &captures_; }
723 void add_capture(RegExpCapture* capture, Zone* zone) {
724 captures_.Add(capture, zone);
725 }
726 const ZoneVector<base::uc16>* name() const { return name_; }
727 void set_name(const ZoneVector<base::uc16>* name) { name_ = name; }
728
729 private:
730 ZoneList<RegExpCapture*> captures_;
731 const ZoneVector<base::uc16>* name_ = nullptr;
732};
